Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *AI Software Engineer* position with *Ampcus Inc.* I bring over three years of professional experience designing and deploying production-grade AI systems — including LLM integrations, agentic AI workflows, and orchestration pipelines — along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my engineering roles, I have built and delivered the exact systems this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph, enabling scalable agentic AI workflows and reliable coordination of autonomous agents across complex customer tasks. I also developed and deployed an MCP AI interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and secure execution across a distributed microservices surface. To keep these AI systems production-ready, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks, while optimizing agent concurrency to reduce end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I built an LLM-powered support chatbot using LangChain and RAG with PostgreSQL as a vector database, and designed a cloud-agnostic storage service in Python deployed across AWS and GCP — giving me direct, hands-on experience with the backend systems, cloud platforms, and database technologies central to this role.

My research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in deep learning model development and generative AI. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I fine-tuned StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion models using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on an HPC cluster, then deployed them via vLLM and Hugging Face for efficient LLM inference. I also led workshops on building AI agents with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith for 50+ students — demonstrating both the technical depth and the collaborative communication skills that reflect the engineering discipline and knowledge-sharing culture Ampcus values.

I have always been passionate about delivering *innovative, cost-effective technology solutions* and building *responsible AI systems* that create positive impact — values that sit at the core of Ampcus's mission. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

